The paper focuses on data-driven models for grounded language understanding in robotics, specifically in the context of semantic mapping and mobile manipulation in partially observable environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for perception and language understanding, which are common in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of language as a sensor, which falls under the Language and Vision (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques for perception, which is relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for language understanding, which is relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
